<p class="wikiPara">
I'll be demo'ing <a href="http://tools.hibernate.org" target="" class="regularLink">Hibernate Tools </a> at
<a href="http://www.eclipsecon.org" target="" class="regularLink">EclipseCon </a> on March 21st. See details <a href="http://www.eclipsecon.org/2006/Sub.do?id=513" target="" class="regularLink">here </a>.
</p>

<p class="wikiPara">
It is a 15 minute demo, so will be a quick'n'dirty presentation; but it will give you a good insight on what
is available via the plugins <a href="http://www.hibernate.org/hib_docs/tools/reference/en/html_single/" target="" class="regularLink">currently </a> and what is <a href="http://opensource2.atlassian.com/projects/hibernate/browse/HBX?report=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.project:roadmap-panel" target="" class="regularLink">coming </a>.
</p>

<p class="wikiPara">
Koen Aers will also be presenting <a href="http://www.eclipsecon.org/2006/Sub.do?id=71" target="" class="regularLink">A Gentle Introduction to GEF </a> 
which is used in the basis of the jBPM designer which can be used to model 
<a href="http://docs.jboss.com/seam/reference/en/html/tools.html#d0e4582" target="" class="regularLink">business processes and pageflow </a> for
<a href="http://www.jboss.com/products/seam" target="" class="regularLink">JBoss Seam </a>.
</p>

<p class="wikiPara">
Marshall Culpepper is also present thus the core team behind <a href="http://www.jboss.org/products/jbosside" target="" class="regularLink">JBoss Eclipse IDE </a> will be there.
</p>
